      "body": "> AuthCookieResult::ERROR -> AuthCookieResult::ERR [The added Doxygen @retval AuthCookieResult::ERROR uses a non-existent enumerator name; the enum is ERR, so this would confuse readers about the intended return value.]\r\n\r\nThe LLM reminds me that `ERROR` (or any upper case name) may break when a windows (or other) header defines an `ERROR` macro, so I wonder if they can be changed to be CamelCase (Err, Ok, and Disabled).",
